         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">20/2/84. ¶  ¶ Let me thank you, dear Prof. Gray, for your lucid remarks on D.C's last publication concerning nomenclature. ¶  I had written some notes for the bot. Centralblatt ¶  soon after receiving...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.02.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Asa Gray</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Gray Herbarium Archives, Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/2/84.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me thank you, dear Prof. Gray, for your lucid remarks on D.C's last publication concerning nomenclature.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A. Gray (1883), commenting on A. de Candolle (1883).</p>
               </note> I had written some notes for the bot. Centralblatt<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B84.04.05.</p>
               </note> soon after receiving the work from M. Alph. de Candolle himself. I may be induced to write still further on the subject; but on this occasion I would merely remark, that I agree with you on <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nearly</hi>
               </seg> all points. You have however overlooked one important moment in regard to the special case of <name key="Stylidium">Stylidium</name>, <name key="Marlea">Marlea</name> and <name key="Candollea">Candollea</name>; it is this: <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name> absorbs <name key="Candollea">Candollea</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>; so we would still need a genus for the great name of D.C., and where is the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fixity</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">without</hi>
               </seg> priority? <name key="Stylidium">Stylidium</name> is for this a good instance to point to.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, that in serenity of mind and firm health you continue your great labors.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have only Rays method in the second edition,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Ray (1703). The copy at the Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne, which was presumably M's though it bears no marks of his ownership, is of the 1710 Amsterdam reprinting of this edition.</p>
               </note> but on enquiry in Europe I was told, that he already in the first (1682) used the terms Di- and <name key="Monocotyledonae">Monocotyledonae</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">See M to B. Daydon Jackson, 25 December 1881 and </seg>M to B. Daydon Jackson, 22 November 1882 (in this edition as 82-11-22b).</p>
               </note> Hence I put them that way in the "Census".<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B83.03.04.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Could you not give us a Census for the U.S. as a precursor and facilitator of a new universal Flora?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Candollea">Candollea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Marlea">Marlea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Monocotyledonae">Monocotyledonae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Stylidium">Stylidium</name>
            </p>
